    • Method Detail

      • orderCapability

        public IndexOrderCapability orderCapability​(ValueCategory... valueCategories)
        Description copied from interface: IndexCapability
        What possible orderings is this index capable to provide for a query on given combination of ValueCategory. Ordering of ValueCategory correspond to ordering of related SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds().
        Specified by:
        orderCapability in interface IndexCapability
        Parameters:
        valueCategories - Ordered array of ValueCategories for which index should be queried. Note that valueCategory must correspond to related SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds(). A null value in the array (new ValueCategory[]{null}) is interpreted as a wildcard for any ValueCategory. Note that this is not the same as order(null) which is undefined.
        Returns:
        IndexOrder array containing all possible orderings for provided value categories or empty array if no explicit ordering is possible or if length of valueCategories and SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds() differ.

      • valueCapability

        public IndexValueCapability valueCapability​(ValueCategory... valueCategories)
        Description copied from interface: IndexCapability
        Is the index capable of providing values for a query on given combination of ValueCategory. Ordering of ValueCategory correspond to ordering of SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds().
        Specified by:
        valueCapability in interface IndexCapability
        Parameters:
        valueCategories - Ordered array of ValueCategories for which index should be queried. Note that valueCategory must correspond to related SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds(). ValueCategory.UNKNOWN can be used as a wildcard for any ValueCategory. Behaviour is undefined for empty null array and null values in array.
        Returns:
        IndexValueCapability.YES if index is capable of providing values for query on provided array of value categories, IndexValueCapability.NO if not or IndexValueCapability.PARTIAL for some results. If length of valueCategories and SchemaDescriptor.getPropertyIds() differ IndexValueCapability.NO is returned.

      • behaviours

        public IndexBehaviour[] behaviours()
        Specified by:
        behaviours in interface IndexCapability
        Returns:
        an array of behaviours that are particular to the implementation or configuration of this index. It could be anything that planning could look at and either try to avoid, seek out, or issue warning for.
